00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 29=

3
00:01:42,420 --> 00:01:42,940
Welcome.

4
00:01:42,940 --> 00:01:44,980
(Dida Ride Hailing)

5
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:45,900
Here.

6
00:01:46,060 --> 00:01:46,460
Thank you.

7
00:01:47,260 --> 00:01:47,660
Thank you.

8
00:01:50,260 --> 00:01:51,420
Not off work yet, Mr. He?

9
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,488
I keep the regular spot for you.

10
00:01:54,060 --> 00:01:54,860
Alright, thanks.

11
00:02:02,733 --> 00:02:04,288
(The building across these windows)

12
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:05,820
(is Lin Zhanqiao's office.)

13
00:02:06,740 --> 00:02:08,180
(Back when He Han stayed here,)

14
00:02:08,355 --> 00:02:09,860
(it was probably because of that.)

15
00:02:22,577 --> 00:02:24,333
(That's why I want you to move in here.)

16
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:26,540
(Once this place slowly becomes yours,)

17
00:02:26,820 --> 00:02:28,100
(once you sleep in that bed)

18
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:29,555
(without thinking about him anymore,)

19
00:02:29,660 --> 00:02:30,540
(that'll mean...)

20
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:33,060
You've completely replaced He Han.

21
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:53,570
Dida has assigned you

22
00:02:53,570 --> 00:02:55,460
a passenger with
the last four digits 3118.

23
00:02:55,580 --> 00:02:58,340
Please follow the navigation
to the pickup location.

24
00:02:58,500 --> 00:02:59,450
Dida reminds you.

25
00:02:59,450 --> 00:03:00,860
Please avoid driving while tired

26
00:03:00,940 --> 00:03:02,300
and drive safely.

27
00:03:02,911 --> 00:03:03,900
Sir, your car is here.

28
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:07,260
This one.

29
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:08,540
Sure. I'll walk you over.

30
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:12,180
Thank you.

31
00:03:12,460 --> 00:03:12,860
Take care.

32
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:14,220
Hello.

33
00:03:18,488 --> 00:03:19,420
What a coincidence.

34
00:03:25,244 --> 00:03:27,222
Please fasten your seat belt.
We're setting off.

35
00:03:36,180 --> 00:03:38,100
Do you usually drive around
this hotel area?

36
00:03:39,244 --> 00:03:40,500
I know this area pretty well.

37
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:42,820
And I know the hotel staff outside, too.

38
00:03:42,820 --> 00:03:44,577
He always saves me a good parking spot.

39
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:47,340
Do you know

40
00:03:48,020 --> 00:03:48,820
why I came here?

41
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:51,020
How would I know?

42
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:51,940
Why?

43
00:03:52,980 --> 00:03:54,460
I'm looking for a new place to write.

44
00:03:58,266 --> 00:04:00,244
The room I stayed in
is actually pretty nice.

45
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:01,340
Yeah, it is.

46
00:04:02,311 --> 00:04:03,400
And expensive, too.

47
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:04,820
Too expensive.

48
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:07,460
If I were you, I would switch hotels.

49
00:04:07,688 --> 00:04:10,088
There are plenty of places
cheaper and better than that one.

50
00:04:10,380 --> 00:04:11,740
Would it bother you

51
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:13,700
if I stayed here?

52
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:15,540
No. Why would it?

53
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,460
Other people stayed in that room

54
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:19,180
before I did, too.

55
00:04:19,380 --> 00:04:20,140
After I leave,

56
00:04:20,140 --> 00:04:22,020
someone else will stay there anyway.

57
00:04:22,711 --> 00:04:24,733
I was more worried
you'd feel uncomfortable.

58
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:27,140
Like you said,

59
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:28,900
it's just a hotel,

60
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:29,820
right?

61
00:04:31,888 --> 00:04:33,777
People are going to talk about you.

62
00:04:36,222 --> 00:04:38,422
The person who'll probably
feel that worst about it

63
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:40,420
is Lin Zhanqiao.

64
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:43,820
She won't.

65
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,644
She'll just look down on you.

66
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:49,780
(Once this place slowly becomes yours,)

67
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,220
(then no matter)

68
00:04:51,220 --> 00:04:52,955
whether you face Lin Zhanqiao or He Han,

69
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:55,300
you'll feel like you deserve
the best treatment

70
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,688
and the highest respect.

71
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:03,660
We're almost there.

72
00:05:03,888 --> 00:05:05,377
Where do you want me to stop?

73
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:07,311
Pull over on the right
after the turn ahead.

74
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,180
Wait downstairs for me.

75
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,220
Don't end the trip.

76
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:13,200
I need to head out again later.

77
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:14,500
Sure.

78
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,860
About how long will you be?

79
00:05:16,977 --> 00:05:18,600
I need to figure out where to park.

80
00:05:19,020 --> 00:05:19,980
Pull over anywhere.

81
00:05:21,044 --> 00:05:22,355
Let the meter keep running.

82
00:05:22,511 --> 00:05:24,333
I'll tell you when I'm coming back out.

83
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:25,780
Got it.

84
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,360
(Market Influence Analysis)
From the current situation,

85
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:31,288
all three projects
have their own strengths.

86
00:05:31,355 --> 00:05:32,740
Year of Blessings is a popular genre

87
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:33,940
with a stable readership.

88
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:35,420
Out of the three projects,

89
00:05:35,977 --> 00:05:36,820
it's the safest bet.

90
00:05:36,888 --> 00:05:38,666
Order of the Mountain Ghost
is a rare genre

91
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:39,977
in the current market.

92
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,820
I think it's a pretty risky attempt.

93
00:05:42,977 --> 00:05:43,530
Of course,

94
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:45,420
it has caught readers' attention.

95
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:46,580
But it's still niche

96
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:47,600
and not very stable yet.

97
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:49,180
I think we should observe it

98
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:49,955
a bit longer.

99
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,220
As for Lord Cui Wei,

100
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:53,900
it's the first title
in one of our key series.

101
00:05:53,977 --> 00:05:55,220
A very important starting point.

102
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:56,460
If this book succeeds,

103
00:05:56,580 --> 00:05:59,177
it'll drive the development
of the entire series going forward.

104
00:05:59,266 --> 00:05:59,777
Ms. Lin,

105
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:01,740
all three project editors
are here today.

106
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,311
Honestly, we're all worried

107
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,300
the company's going to cut
our promotion budgets.

108
00:06:09,222 --> 00:06:10,620
Let me be upfront with everyone

109
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,180
about my plans.

110
00:06:13,660 --> 00:06:15,500
If I can keep Gu Yan

111
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,620
at Chenxing,

112
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:19,500
then every plan we made before

113
00:06:19,555 --> 00:06:21,066
will continue as scheduled.

114
00:06:21,420 --> 00:06:22,540
But if he insists on leaving,

115
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,020
I'll receive a payout.

116
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:25,940
And the most important thing for us

117
00:06:26,044 --> 00:06:27,050
will be using that money

118
00:06:27,050 --> 00:06:29,088
to push one project
into becoming a top-tier hit.

119
00:06:29,288 --> 00:06:30,288
So during this period,

120
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:32,490
I'll definitely cut the budgets
for the other projects.

121
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:33,155
Understood?

122
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:35,911
Year of the Blessings is the safest bet
with the quickest return.

123
00:06:35,980 --> 00:06:37,950
But film studios have kept an eye
on Lord Cui Wei

124
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,260
and are actively following up.

125
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,020
There's a real chance
its adaptation rights

126
00:06:41,020 --> 00:06:42,733
could be sold for a very high price.

127
00:06:42,822 --> 00:06:44,150
Order of the Ghost Mountain
is my project.

128
00:06:44,180 --> 00:06:45,540
I'm not just speaking up
for myself here,

129
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:48,400
but with how saturated the market is
with similar genres right now,

130
00:06:48,488 --> 00:06:50,140
if we want to stand out, Ms. Lin,

131
00:06:50,220 --> 00:06:52,577
I think you should give
Order of the Mountain Ghost a push.

132
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:53,500
But if Lord Cui Wei

133
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:54,540
successfully sells

134
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:55,660
its screen adaptation rights,

135
00:06:55,822 --> 00:06:56,980
the licensing fee could also

136
00:06:56,980 --> 00:06:58,360
be used to support other projects.

137
00:06:58,370 --> 00:06:59,860
But Lord Cui Wei is in its early stages.

138
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:01,780
It'll need long-term
and consistent promotion.

139
00:07:01,866 --> 00:07:03,170
Year of the Blessings is more
than halfway through serialization,

140
00:07:03,170 --> 00:07:04,400
and the author's still going strong.

141
00:07:04,460 --> 00:07:05,850
If we prioritize promoting
Year of the Blessings,

142
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:07,100
we'll see returns much faster.

143
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:09,620
There are too many similar titles
in the market for this.

144
00:07:09,844 --> 00:07:12,911
Honestly, its story doesn't have
the strength to become a top-tier hit.

145
00:07:14,177 --> 00:07:15,111
Pull over here.

146
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:52,700
I'm not denying
it can become a first-tier title.

147
00:07:52,710 --> 00:07:53,690
(Gu Yan)
But the story itself

148
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,850
doesn't have the potential
to become a breakout phenomenon.

149
00:07:55,860 --> 00:07:57,977
The payoff just isn't worth it
if you do that math.

150
00:07:58,500 --> 00:07:59,260
I still think...

151
00:07:59,540 --> 00:07:59,900
Hello?

152
00:08:00,340 --> 00:08:02,340
Guys, I think we should prioritize...

153
00:08:02,780 --> 00:08:03,620
I'm free now.

154
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:04,380
Come over.

155
00:08:04,577 --> 00:08:05,340
I'll be right there.

156
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:11,777
Whether it's Lord Cui Wei
or Order of the Mountain Ghost...

157
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:13,420
I'm going to see Gu Yan first.

158
00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:14,755
Wait for me to get back.

159
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,300
That's really a surprise, Wang Hai.

160
00:08:24,422 --> 00:08:26,250
I never expected you
to do something like this

161
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:27,244
for my wedding gift.

162
00:08:28,911 --> 00:08:30,380
I thought now that you've made money,

163
00:08:30,460 --> 00:08:31,580
(Mengtong Internet Cafe Renovation Plan)
you would give us a red packet,

164
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:33,540
or maybe some gold jewelry.

165
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:34,860
I even thought

166
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:36,300
you might buy Er Jiu a car.

167
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:37,900
But you actually hired someone

168
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:39,533
to renovate our internet cafe.

169
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,380
This was from Zhao Lanxin?

170
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:42,860
Yeah.

171
00:08:42,911 --> 00:08:44,580
She said you wanted to keep it a secret.

172
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:47,260
But since Er Jiu and I are the ones
using the internet cafe,

173
00:08:47,340 --> 00:08:48,770
she thought we'd see the plans
in advance.

174
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:49,860
Before the design is finalized,

175
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:52,244
we can point out anything we don't like
and change it early.

176
00:08:52,380 --> 00:08:53,460
She's thoughtful.

177
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,780
She also said you've made plans

178
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:56,900
for our future.

179
00:08:57,140 --> 00:08:58,780
Like a chain of e-sports hotels

180
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:00,460
and building our own e-sports team.

181
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:07,260
Thank you, Wang Hai.

182
00:09:10,340 --> 00:09:11,740
Why didn't you tell me yourself?

183
00:09:11,888 --> 00:09:14,511
She said you've always
been planning things for us.

184
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:18,180
I should thank Zhao Lanxin.

185
00:09:19,380 --> 00:09:20,620
I did have that wish.

186
00:09:22,060 --> 00:09:23,700
She's the one who helped make it happen.

187
00:09:26,977 --> 00:09:27,977
Take a look.

188
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:38,860
(Moments)

189
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:41,244
(Cai Zhangzhu: In the name of the Moon,
I'll punish the ungrateful one)

190
00:09:41,288 --> 00:09:42,260
(three hundred times.)

191
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:59,180
(What happened?)

192
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:13,700
Hello?

193
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:15,100
Hello, Mr. He Han?

194
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:16,740
It's about Gu Yan.

195
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:19,940
Do you have time now?

196
00:10:19,940 --> 00:10:20,820
Can we talk for a bit?

197
00:10:21,244 --> 00:10:22,540
I'm seriously about to explode.

198
00:10:22,822 --> 00:10:23,860
I'm very free right now.

199
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:26,580
Anyone can tell
you're talking about Gu Yan.

200
00:10:26,580 --> 00:10:27,400
What happened?

201
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:29,133
Do you know
what he has done to Ms. Lin?

202
00:10:29,140 --> 00:10:31,420
He summons her whenever he wants
and dismisses her just as easily.

203
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:33,111
He doesn't give her any respect at all.

204
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,620
Do you know why I have time

205
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:36,420
to call you right now?

206
00:10:37,860 --> 00:10:38,940
Because Ms. Lin

207
00:10:39,860 --> 00:10:42,300
went to beg Gu Yan
not to leave Chenxing.

208
00:10:42,820 --> 00:10:44,380
Beg him? Can you imagine that?

209
00:11:07,380 --> 00:11:08,500
What did you just say? Go on.

210
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,620
(Hello, when would you like to depart?)

211
00:12:01,540 --> 00:12:03,260
(The driver
has been waiting for one hour.)

212
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:07,780
(Zhao Lanxin)

213
00:12:53,220 --> 00:12:55,980
(Hello, when would you like to depart?)

214
00:13:22,060 --> 00:13:22,900
You got here fast.

215
00:13:26,511 --> 00:13:28,733
I came straight over
right after we hung up.

216
00:13:32,044 --> 00:13:33,555
What do you want to tell me?

217
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:52,780
I take back what I said before.

218
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:56,500
I hope you'll consider

219
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:00,066
continuing to work with Chenxing

220
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:02,380
while also working

221
00:14:03,140 --> 00:14:05,340
with Dingqi and Zhao Lanxin.

222
00:14:05,911 --> 00:14:08,400
I'll probably need to discuss that
with Zhao Lanxin.

223
00:14:10,288 --> 00:14:12,222
We haven't terminated our contract yet.

224
00:14:13,311 --> 00:14:15,140
You haven't signed with
Zhao Lanxin either.

225
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:18,380
Whatever decision you make,

226
00:14:19,140 --> 00:14:21,180
you don't need to discuss it with her.

227
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:23,100
She has done a lot for me.

228
00:14:23,620 --> 00:14:24,300
Just today,

229
00:14:24,940 --> 00:14:25,500
just now,

230
00:14:26,377 --> 00:14:28,100
she was still making arrangements
for me.

231
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:29,900
She even considered

232
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:31,866
the guilt I feel toward
San Mei and Er Jiu.

233
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:42,420
Fine.

234
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:48,422
I admit Zhao Lanxin
has done a lot for you.

235
00:14:50,020 --> 00:14:51,500
That's why you want to work with her.

236
00:14:58,180 --> 00:14:58,940
I accept that.

237
00:15:11,740 --> 00:15:12,300
Like I said,

238
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:16,060
I came here today

239
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:21,300
hoping that

240
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:24,660
for the sake of me discovering you,

241
00:15:26,844 --> 00:15:29,066
for the sake of how hard
we worked together

242
00:15:29,420 --> 00:15:31,940
to finally succeed,

243
00:15:33,844 --> 00:15:35,666
you could continue working with Chenxing

244
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,740
for another year or two.

245
00:15:42,288 --> 00:15:44,244
She still has responsibilities
for Chenxing.

246
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,755
She'll definitely come back

247
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:47,260
and beg you.

248
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:52,300
Lin Zhanqiao,

249
00:15:55,088 --> 00:15:57,100
have you never begged anyone
like this before?

250
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:01,700
Did you rehearse this speech
over and over beforehand?

251
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:05,820
Zhao Lanxin predicted all of this.

252
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:25,140
I prepared more than this.

253
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:29,460
If I were a man,

254
00:16:30,580 --> 00:16:31,380
I would probably

255
00:16:31,380 --> 00:16:32,980
be pouring you drink after drink

256
00:16:33,340 --> 00:16:34,660
until you agreed.

257
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:37,140
Too bad I'm not.

258
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:39,580
So all I can do is talk.

259
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:45,860
But honestly,

260
00:16:45,860 --> 00:16:47,500
I don't have much more left to say.

261
00:16:48,955 --> 00:16:50,111
No matter how I put it,

262
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:52,620
I'm just asking you to help me

263
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:56,260
and Chenxing get through this.

264
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:05,140
I'll owe you one.

265
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:08,100
I'll repay it.

266
00:17:24,380 --> 00:17:26,220
Boss, I'm ready to order.

267
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:56,020
I'm not used to seeing
this side of you, Lin Zhanqiao.

268
00:17:58,660 --> 00:17:59,580
I can't agree to it.

269
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:02,580
Because I already promised
Zhao Lanxin.

270
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:04,700
Everything you just said...

271
00:18:06,155 --> 00:18:07,600
Zhao Lanxin heard it, too.

272
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:09,540
If she agrees,

273
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,470
I'm willing to discuss with you.

274
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:12,900
What do you mean?

275
00:18:18,580 --> 00:18:21,260
(Zhao Lanxin)

276
00:18:28,660 --> 00:18:29,860
How could you do this?

277
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:33,700
No matter how you treated me,
I could accept it.

278
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:35,020
I was prepared for that.

279
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:37,620
But why would you do something
this disgusting?

280
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:39,666
I was on the phone with her
when I came back.

281
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:40,980
She told me not to hang up.

282
00:18:41,311 --> 00:18:42,700
She was afraid that if I saw you,

283
00:18:43,180 --> 00:18:43,860
I would go soft.

284
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:46,340
Lin Zhanqiao,

285
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:49,250
Zhao Lanxin was wrong.

286
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:50,140
Do you realize

287
00:18:50,155 --> 00:18:51,800
how shameless and despicable this is?

288
00:18:52,220 --> 00:18:53,340
Zhao Lanxin also said

289
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:56,940
that if you cried in front of me,

290
00:18:57,866 --> 00:18:59,220
I could agree to help you.

291
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:01,820
I won't.

292
00:19:03,155 --> 00:19:04,177
You're not worth it.

293
00:19:44,140 --> 00:19:45,133
Where's Lin Zhanqiao?

294
00:19:45,177 --> 00:19:46,200
Why haven't you left yet?

295
00:19:46,220 --> 00:19:46,700
Seriously?

296
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,688
How could I leave
before you end the order?

297
00:19:48,940 --> 00:19:49,860
Where's Lin Zhanqiao?

298
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:50,820
She left.

299
00:19:54,555 --> 00:19:55,540
Didn't you want to know

300
00:19:55,540 --> 00:19:56,660
why Lin Zhanqiao came?

301
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:58,260
I'll tell you.

302
00:19:59,180 --> 00:20:00,100
She came to beg me.

303
00:20:00,460 --> 00:20:01,533
Didn't expect that, right?

304
00:20:08,860 --> 00:20:10,800
Of course you should
help her when she asks.

305
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:14,500
Without her,
you would be nothing right now.

306
00:20:14,780 --> 00:20:15,900
Now that she's in trouble,

307
00:20:16,266 --> 00:20:17,533
why didn't she ask you for help?

308
00:20:17,740 --> 00:20:18,860
If she begged you for help,

309
00:20:18,860 --> 00:20:20,466
you would definitely help her, right?

310
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:22,060
But she would rather come to me.

311
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:24,177
Even if I refuse,
she'll still come back to me.

312
00:20:24,780 --> 00:20:26,420
Do you understand
how worthless you are?

313
00:20:32,933 --> 00:20:34,488
You and Lin Zhanqiao are the same!

314
00:20:34,940 --> 00:20:36,260
Both of you are worthless.

315
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:08,140
I couldn't persuade Gu Yan.

316
00:21:10,260 --> 00:21:10,860
I'm sorry.

317
00:21:13,020 --> 00:21:15,140
Think about which
of those three projects

318
00:21:15,300 --> 00:21:16,300
we're going to push.

319
00:21:37,580 --> 00:21:37,940
Hello?

320
00:21:43,940 --> 00:21:44,740
Yes, this is.

321
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:12,700
(Police)

322
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:19,420
(Ningping Road Police Station)

323
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:20,260
Are you okay?

324
00:22:20,460 --> 00:22:21,100
I'm fine.

325
00:22:24,340 --> 00:22:25,660
Why did you hit him?

326
00:22:26,180 --> 00:22:27,460
Doesn't he deserve it?

327
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:30,620
Beating him up won't solve anything.

328
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:31,900
It does. It felt good.

329
00:22:32,088 --> 00:22:33,330
I just wanted him to know there are

330
00:22:33,330 --> 00:22:34,990
consequences
for doing something like that.

331
00:22:35,044 --> 00:22:36,750
It'll teach him
some sense of right and wrong.

332
00:22:37,688 --> 00:22:39,644
But you've been to
the police station now.

333
00:22:39,755 --> 00:22:41,688
Can you still drive
for the platform after this?

334
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:43,490
I don't know.

335
00:22:43,490 --> 00:22:45,333
Depends on how the platform handles it.

336
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:46,500
Maybe not.

337
00:22:47,888 --> 00:22:49,466
Then what are you going to do?

338
00:22:49,555 --> 00:22:51,610
If this platform doesn't work out,
there'll be others.

339
00:22:51,622 --> 00:22:52,670
I'll figure something out.

340
00:22:53,860 --> 00:22:54,660
I can drive for you.

341
00:22:55,620 --> 00:22:56,540
No need. I'm fine.

342
00:23:27,980 --> 00:23:29,540
If you can't drive anymore,

343
00:23:30,580 --> 00:23:31,660
come back to writing.

344
00:23:32,340 --> 00:23:33,340
Don't worry about me.

345
00:23:33,420 --> 00:23:34,540
Worry about yourself instead.

346
00:23:34,540 --> 00:23:36,133
What are you planning to do next?

347
00:23:37,777 --> 00:23:40,190
I'm betting everything on a project
that hasn't launched yet.

348
00:23:40,580 --> 00:23:41,420
If it works,

349
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:42,860
then I'll have a shot

350
00:23:43,180 --> 00:23:44,800
at getting funding from investors.

351
00:23:45,780 --> 00:23:47,060
But if it fails,

352
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:48,500
then forget it.

353
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,488
That's it for Chenxing.

354
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,333
Doesn't Gu Yan owe you
compensation for breach of contract?

355
00:23:56,844 --> 00:23:59,666
Yeah, but both sides are still
gathering evidence through lawyers

356
00:23:59,820 --> 00:24:00,700
and filing lawsuits.

357
00:24:01,488 --> 00:24:02,940
By the time everything's settled,

358
00:24:02,940 --> 00:24:04,333
and the money actually comes in,

359
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:06,380
it'll probably take at least
another year or more.

360
00:24:14,260 --> 00:24:15,260
Objectively speaking,

361
00:24:16,340 --> 00:24:18,100
how's that new project looking?

362
00:24:20,577 --> 00:24:22,511
It's the best option
among limited choices.

363
00:24:22,555 --> 00:24:24,610
I mean how confident are you
that you can pull it off?

364
00:24:24,620 --> 00:24:26,060
Seventy percent? Three percent?

365
00:24:26,355 --> 00:24:27,800
Big rewards come from big risks.

366
00:24:31,460 --> 00:24:32,860
What's the new novel called?

367
00:24:33,822 --> 00:24:36,244
It's a novel about myth and revival
aimed at female readers.

368
00:24:37,044 --> 00:24:38,600
You wouldn't be interested.

369
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:43,020
If Gu Yan gives you trouble again,

370
00:24:43,020 --> 00:24:43,900
call me.

371
00:24:43,980 --> 00:24:44,740
He won't.

372
00:24:45,020 --> 00:24:45,420
I'm off.

373
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,355
(Ms. Lin, are you okay?)

374
00:25:50,300 --> 00:25:52,780
(I'm fine. Good night.)

375
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:16,060
♪Like a drifting dandelion♪

376
00:26:16,060 --> 00:26:16,980
(To this day,)

377
00:26:18,060 --> 00:26:19,060
(Chenxing's downfall)

378
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:20,580
(is unavoidable.)

379
00:26:22,740 --> 00:26:24,100
(I may be a good editor.)

380
00:26:25,740 --> 00:26:26,540
(Organized,)

381
00:26:27,340 --> 00:26:28,100
(planned,)

382
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:31,500
(hardworking, and resilient.)

383
00:26:32,844 --> 00:26:34,300
(But none of those qualities)

384
00:26:35,020 --> 00:26:36,900
(were enough to make me a good boss.)

385
00:26:37,060 --> 00:26:42,740
♪Even spring borrows its fragrance♪

386
00:26:43,220 --> 00:26:44,355
(Refusal to compromise)

387
00:26:45,066 --> 00:26:46,180
(or take a step back.)

388
00:26:47,220 --> 00:26:48,540
(My ego and stubbornness)

389
00:26:49,700 --> 00:26:51,500
(left both Chenxing and me shattered)

390
00:26:52,740 --> 00:26:53,740
(when we hit obstacles.)

391
00:26:58,700 --> 00:27:05,460
♪Swaying in the shape of the wind♪

392
00:27:05,940 --> 00:27:10,740
♪Not waiting for calm to come♪

393
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:13,820
Zhangzhu, what's the title
of that new novel

394
00:27:13,820 --> 00:27:15,422
your company's planning to promote?

395
00:27:36,140 --> 00:27:38,340
First is a welcome speech
and company introduction.

396
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:39,660
Second is the training plan.

397
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:39,940
Hello?

398
00:27:40,244 --> 00:27:41,622
Have you reached the office yet?

399
00:27:41,820 --> 00:27:42,580
I'm in a meeting.

400
00:27:42,900 --> 00:27:44,260
Going over HR details.

401
00:27:44,488 --> 00:27:46,155
What about you? Is Guangzhou hot?

402
00:27:47,060 --> 00:27:48,580
I'm fine. I haven't been outside much.

403
00:27:48,911 --> 00:27:51,355
I just met with an author
and got back to the hotel.

404
00:27:52,060 --> 00:27:53,340
Have HR send me an email

405
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:54,780
about the new employees.

406
00:27:54,780 --> 00:27:55,866
I want to take a look.

407
00:27:59,340 --> 00:28:00,780
It's room service bringing breakfast.

408
00:28:06,511 --> 00:28:08,688
My flight back to Shanghai
is tomorrow at noon.

409
00:28:08,940 --> 00:28:09,844
See you tomorrow.

410
00:28:10,300 --> 00:28:10,740
What?

411
00:28:10,866 --> 00:28:12,933
You told Ling Yikai
you weren't in Shanghai?

412
00:28:12,955 --> 00:28:15,300
I told him I was on a business trip
in Guangzhou for three days,

413
00:28:15,311 --> 00:28:16,111
meeting an author.

414
00:28:17,155 --> 00:28:18,180
I brought you some food.

415
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:18,940
Thanks.

416
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:22,340
Why didn't you tell him you had surgery?

417
00:28:23,660 --> 00:28:24,580
He doesn't want kids.

418
00:28:24,933 --> 00:28:26,460
He thinks I've been
taking birth control,

419
00:28:26,460 --> 00:28:27,866
so I couldn't get pregnant.

420
00:28:28,488 --> 00:28:30,420
You've been staying here
these three days?

421
00:28:32,020 --> 00:28:32,900
You're the only person

422
00:28:32,900 --> 00:28:33,860
I told about this place.

423
00:28:34,422 --> 00:28:36,622
Lin Zhanqiao said she saw you
at the hospital.

424
00:28:37,577 --> 00:28:39,500
She probably doesn't know
why I was there.

425
00:28:40,577 --> 00:28:41,740
You didn't tell her, did you?

426
00:28:42,100 --> 00:28:42,620
No.

427
00:28:43,660 --> 00:28:44,860
I haven't seen her either.

428
00:28:45,644 --> 00:28:47,644
Besides, this is your private business.

429
00:28:48,980 --> 00:28:49,420
Thanks.

430
00:28:51,266 --> 00:28:53,866
Right now, the person
she probably hates most is me.

431
00:28:54,580 --> 00:28:55,620
But she should understand

432
00:28:55,822 --> 00:28:58,422
that in any industry, if you want
to climb all the way to the top,

433
00:28:58,500 --> 00:29:00,266
(Registration and Consultation Slip)
you run into countless competitors.

434
00:29:00,270 --> 00:29:01,990
(Post-Hysteroscopy Care Instructions)
We just happened to be placed

435
00:29:02,022 --> 00:29:03,333
on opposite sides by fate.

436
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:04,780
And there's only one trophy.

437
00:29:06,060 --> 00:29:07,020
The trophy matters.

438
00:29:07,380 --> 00:29:08,420
So does your life.

439
00:29:09,100 --> 00:29:11,280
The doctor said you have
to rest in bed for three days

440
00:29:11,580 --> 00:29:13,260
and no strenuous activity for a month.

441
00:29:14,300 --> 00:29:14,780
I know.

442
00:29:16,177 --> 00:29:17,220
But I'm not like you guys.

443
00:29:17,340 --> 00:29:18,020
I'm tough.

444
00:29:19,660 --> 00:29:21,460
If you need to go to the hospital
next time,

445
00:29:22,140 --> 00:29:22,940
call me.

446
00:29:23,300 --> 00:29:24,100
I'll go with you.

447
00:29:25,155 --> 00:29:26,500
Next time I go to the hospital,

448
00:29:26,500 --> 00:29:28,444
I'll probably be
for a pregnancy check-up.

449
00:29:28,911 --> 00:29:30,660
I thought Ling Yikai didn't want kids.

450
00:29:34,180 --> 00:29:34,620
I do.

451
00:29:37,540 --> 00:29:39,860
(In the little town of Hulan River)

452
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:41,940
(lived my grandpa.)

453
00:29:42,940 --> 00:29:44,060
(By the time I was born,)

454
00:29:44,860 --> 00:29:46,780
(he was over sixty years old.)

455
00:29:48,020 --> 00:29:49,380
(And when I was four or five,)

456
00:29:50,140 --> 00:29:51,700
(he was nearly seventy.)

457
00:29:53,380 --> 00:29:55,140
(We had a big garden at home.)

458
00:29:55,980 --> 00:29:57,420
(In that garden, there were bees,)

459
00:29:58,020 --> 00:29:58,740
(butterflies,)

460
00:29:59,180 --> 00:29:59,980
(dragonflies,)

461
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:01,180
(and grasshoppers.)

462
00:30:01,860 --> 00:30:02,820
(Everything.)

463
00:30:04,180 --> 00:30:06,020
(There were white butterflies)

464
00:30:06,540 --> 00:30:07,460
(and yellow butterflies.)

465
00:30:09,060 --> 00:30:10,500
(Those butterflies were tiny,)

466
00:30:10,580 --> 00:30:11,420
(not very pretty.)

467
00:30:12,380 --> 00:30:13,260
(The beautiful ones)

468
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:15,700
(were the red butterflies.)

469
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:17,900
(Their wings were dusted
with golden powder.)

470
00:30:18,940 --> 00:30:20,820
(The dragonflies were gold.)

471
00:30:21,620 --> 00:30:23,420
(The grasshoppers were green.)

472
00:30:24,380 --> 00:30:25,060
(The bees...)

473
00:30:25,260 --> 00:30:26,620
You're here so early.

474
00:30:26,940 --> 00:30:27,380
Mom.

475
00:30:29,140 --> 00:30:31,340
I wanted to see you
before heading to the office.

476
00:30:31,688 --> 00:30:33,355
Where are Dad and the caretaker?

477
00:30:34,740 --> 00:30:36,340
She's at the market.

478
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:41,340
Since when did you start reading books?

479
00:30:42,500 --> 00:30:43,780
I don't read.

480
00:30:44,540 --> 00:30:45,940
Your dad brought it.

481
00:30:46,860 --> 00:30:48,180
He reads to me.

482
00:30:50,020 --> 00:30:51,020
While reading,

483
00:30:51,620 --> 00:30:53,140
he explains things

484
00:30:53,420 --> 00:30:54,700
like a storyteller.

485
00:30:55,580 --> 00:30:57,860
He spent the whole afternoon reading.

486
00:30:59,540 --> 00:31:00,540
If you like it,

487
00:31:00,700 --> 00:31:01,700
ask him to keep reading.

488
00:31:02,860 --> 00:31:04,380
It's not that I like it.

489
00:31:05,620 --> 00:31:07,580
But the part he read yesterday

490
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:10,020
was actually quite interesting.

491
00:31:11,420 --> 00:31:12,940
So I secretly recorded it.

492
00:31:15,140 --> 00:31:15,860
Today,

493
00:31:16,420 --> 00:31:17,420
I listened to it again.

494
00:31:19,260 --> 00:31:21,380
If he doesn't sit beside me reading,

495
00:31:23,700 --> 00:31:25,620
what else would we even talk about?

496
00:31:27,740 --> 00:31:28,740
There's not much to say.

497
00:31:29,140 --> 00:31:32,460
So reading's better.

498
00:31:34,260 --> 00:31:35,220
Where did he go today?

499
00:31:35,780 --> 00:31:36,955
I gave him the day off.

500
00:31:37,660 --> 00:31:38,860
He can go wherever he wants.

501
00:31:39,620 --> 00:31:41,020
He'll come home for dinner tonight.

502
00:31:41,355 --> 00:31:43,060
That doesn't sound like you, Mom.

503
00:31:44,940 --> 00:31:46,020
If you make him

504
00:31:46,780 --> 00:31:48,260
stay beside me all the time,

505
00:31:49,420 --> 00:31:50,980
don't you think he'd feel miserable?

506
00:31:53,100 --> 00:31:54,660
And when I think about that,

507
00:31:55,140 --> 00:31:56,580
I feel miserable, too.

508
00:32:02,380 --> 00:32:03,460
Once you get better,

509
00:32:03,940 --> 00:32:05,460
you two can go out together.

510
00:32:06,420 --> 00:32:07,780
Whether I'll get better or not,

511
00:32:09,380 --> 00:32:10,180
I don't know.

512
00:32:12,700 --> 00:32:14,540
But if he had to

513
00:32:15,180 --> 00:32:17,420
take me along when he goes out,

514
00:32:18,866 --> 00:32:20,780
he would probably rather
not go anywhere at all.

515
00:32:21,620 --> 00:32:23,140
That much I know for sure.

516
00:32:25,100 --> 00:32:27,020
He's been like this his whole life.

517
00:32:28,620 --> 00:32:31,860
He can't travel happily with anyone.

518
00:32:34,540 --> 00:32:35,220
If...

519
00:32:36,540 --> 00:32:38,220
there had to be one person,

520
00:32:40,140 --> 00:32:41,140
it would be you.

521
00:32:42,500 --> 00:32:43,540
When you were little,

522
00:32:44,580 --> 00:32:46,060
he took you to the zoo,

523
00:32:47,260 --> 00:32:48,100
to Suzhou,

524
00:32:49,180 --> 00:32:50,020
and to Hangzhou.

525
00:32:56,088 --> 00:32:57,555
Do you want to take your meds?

526
00:32:58,900 --> 00:32:59,580
I'm fine.

527
00:33:04,420 --> 00:33:06,220
Massage here for me.

528
00:33:06,340 --> 00:33:06,660
Okay.

529
00:33:09,260 --> 00:33:09,740
Here?

530
00:33:14,780 --> 00:33:15,940
Here.

531
00:33:27,355 --> 00:33:28,820
He's at the Western Suburb Hotel.

532
00:33:30,020 --> 00:33:30,660
I didn't ask.

533
00:33:32,500 --> 00:33:33,740
He sent it himself.

534
00:33:35,500 --> 00:33:36,780
Whenever I let him go out,

535
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:39,620
he sends me pictures.

536
00:33:41,540 --> 00:33:42,300
I feel like

537
00:33:45,180 --> 00:33:46,180
that's his way

538
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:52,100
of repaying me for giving him freedom.

539
00:33:55,380 --> 00:33:55,780
Mom,

540
00:33:58,380 --> 00:33:59,420
I've been thinking.

541
00:34:01,244 --> 00:34:02,933
Everyone probably has a different idea

542
00:34:03,380 --> 00:34:05,180
of the most comfortable distance

543
00:34:06,500 --> 00:34:07,620
in a close relationship.

544
00:34:10,420 --> 00:34:11,540
Your distance

545
00:34:12,220 --> 00:34:13,140
is very close,

546
00:34:14,780 --> 00:34:16,140
and Dad's distance

547
00:34:17,620 --> 00:34:18,500
is very far away.

548
00:34:20,340 --> 00:34:21,180
This kind of thing

549
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:25,420
isn't like weight or height,

550
00:34:25,940 --> 00:34:27,700
where there's a clear number.

551
00:34:29,500 --> 00:34:30,380
If there were,

552
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:32,580
things would be much easier.

553
00:34:34,333 --> 00:34:35,822
People who want to get married

554
00:34:37,060 --> 00:34:39,980
